    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the research and the plan:\n\n## What I Found\n\nBun has a well-established pattern for format namespaces. All four existing ones (`TOML`, `JSONC`, `JSON5`, `YAML`) follow the same 4-layer architecture. Crucially, **an INI parser already exists** in `src/ini.zig`, battle-tested for `.npmrc` parsing. It's just not publicly exposed yet.\n\n## The Plan: 8 File Changes\n\n### New file (1):\n- **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — Core implementation with `create()`, `parse()`, and `stringify()`\n  - `parse()` reuses the existing `ini.Parser` from `src/ini.zig` directly\n  - `stringify()` is new code — implemented using `jsc.JSPropertyIterator` to walk the JS object and emit INI format (scalars first, then `[sections]` for object values)\n\n### Modified files (7):\n1. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** — Export `INIObject`\n2. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — Add `INI` lazy property callback + `getINIObject()` getter\n3. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — Add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER`\n4. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — Add entry to `@begin bunObjectTable`\n5. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — Add `namespace INI { parse, stringify }` type definitions\n6. **`src/js/private.d.ts`** — Add `var INI` to internal declarations\n7. **`test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts`** — Add `Bun.INI` public API tests alongside existing internal tests\n\n## Key Design Decision\nThe `stringify()` method must be written from scratch in `INIObject.zig` (no INI serializer exists yet). It uses a two-pass approach: root-level scalars first, then `[section]` headers for object values — consistent with how the parser deserializes INI.",
